headline: CrowdStrike (CRWD) Valuation Check After Record Q3 Growth and Expanding AI-Driven Cybersecurity Partnerships
summary: CrowdStrike Holdings (CRWD) just delivered a record third quarter, with net new annual recurring revenue and operating income both accelerating as demand for its AI native Falcon platform spreads across cloud, identity, and SIEM security. See our latest analysis for CrowdStrike Holdings. The latest results land after a flurry of product launches and partnerships with AWS, HPE, and Kroll, and the market has largely rewarded that execution, with a roughly 47% year to date share price return and...
